article.description: Delante Jones tied his career high with 23 points and American beat Navy 63-58 on Wednesday night to end the Midshipmen's six-game winning streak.
article.headline: American ends Navy's six-game win streak, 63-58
article.linkText: American ends Navy's six-game win streak, 63-58
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Delante Jones tied his career high with 23 points and American beat Navy 63-58 on Wednesday night to end the Midshipmen's six-game winning streak. American, leading 54-52, scored five straight points, four from Jesse Reed, to begin an 11-6 run in the final minute. Jones was 9 of 14 from the field and hit three 3-pointers. Jalen Rhea scored his 15 points on five 3-pointers and Reed added 12, going 6 of 6 from the free-throw line. The Eagles were 9 of 23 from 3-point range. American (4-15, 2-6 Patriot League) has won two in a row after losing 10 straight. Tilman Dunbar scored 14 points, Jace Hogan 11 and Shawn Anderson 10 for Navy (15-6, 6-2), which was just 2 of 11 on 3-pointers. American pulled off the upset despite coming in as the nation's second-to-last team in scoring offense (54.5) while Navy came in ninth in scoring defense (61.7).
